				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Marr mana regen?<a name="66285"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 10 04 8:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The real question is, how did you manage to get high enough level to have a 3600 mana pool before figuring out that our mana songs don't effect us?  I'm kinda stunned to be honest, I expect that kind of ignorance from non-bards who always seem to be suprised when they hear about it... but a bard with almost 4k mana?  This is what we talk about when we say &quot;know your songs.&quot;  A good bard isn't the one who can twist the most songs, it's the bard who knows exactly what all of his/her songs do and knows when and how to apply them.
<br />

<br />
I don't have a problem with the mana portion not effecting us.  I can Fade 5 times in rapid sucession if need be and the need to do that is so rare that I'm normally at full mana.  When you've got the mana pool and the regen Fade is an essential pulling tool.</span></td>
